Four players from the PSL have been nominated  for CAF Player of the Year award. SuperSport United duo,  Dean Furman and Jeremy Brockie have been nominated for the African player of the year, for players based in Africa. Mamelodi Sundowns players Percy Tau and goalkeeper Denis Onyango have also been nominated for this prestigious award. Tau and Onyango have also been shortlisted for the African Player of the Year award. CAF on Wednesday announced a 30-man shortlist for the African Player of the Year award. African Player of the Year African Player of the Year – Based in Africa -TNA Reporter